    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-04-20T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-04-20T03:00:00-05:00" n="521"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d521">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11889: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Amoy (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_FLW1"
                            type="from">Franklin</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting
                            Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Amoy</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-20T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 20, 1932—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 20—9:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to my telegram of April 19, 3 p.m.,<note n="41" xml:id="d521fn41">Not
                        printed.</note> it is apparently true that Changchow has been captured.
                    Refugees continue to flow into Amoy and International Settlement of Kulangsu.
                    Four British submarines with mother ship arrived this afternoon en route to
                    Weihai-wei for a visit of 3 days. Two Japanese destroyers to have left this
                    morning have received orders to remain here. Americans at Tungan evacuating that
                    place and coming to Kulangsu. My despatch No. 12, dated December 31, 1931, file
                    No. 130.7<note n="41" xml:id="d521fn42">Not printed.</note> gives list of
                    American citizens in this district with their addresses in the United
                    States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_FLW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
